# Micro-Mate (Toledo variant)

Minimal skeleton for Toledo Micro-Mate using Python + pygame and SVG pieces.

Run:
- Desktop (macOS/Linux): python3 -m src.run_game
- Raspberry Pi Zero (framebuffer): sudo SDL_VIDEODRIVER=fbcon SDL_FBDEV=/dev/fb0 python3 -m src.run_game

Controls:
- Left arrow: go backward
- Right arrow: go forward
- R: restart (press Y/Enter to confirm, N/Esc to cancel)
- T: cycle board themes

The current position highlights the last move's from-square and to-square.

Game state is autosaved on exit to `~/.micro-mate/save-state.json` and restored on the next launch.

Place SVG assets in assets/svg/ and run tools/rasterize_assets.py to generate PNGs for Pi packaging.
